1
00:00:07,056 --> 00:00:09,393
LIBERAL FRONTIER PARTY

2
00:00:16,742 --> 00:00:17,744
[sighs]

3
00:00:17,827 --> 00:00:19,413
-Next is at 4 p.m.?
-Yes.

4
00:00:22,378 --> 00:00:23,421
No comment.

5
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:27,263
Mr. Maruyama. Mr. Maruyama!

6
00:00:27,346 --> 00:00:29,350
I might be able to help you.

7
00:00:34,026 --> 00:00:35,279
What is it?

8
00:00:38,451 --> 00:00:39,997
[panting on phone]

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:45,675
[Tanaka] This is the hostess accusing
your brother of sexual assault.

10
00:00:46,259 --> 00:00:47,887
By the way, is this your brother?

11
00:00:49,098 --> 00:00:51,311
-Isn't this Masashi Maruyama?
-Where did you get it?

12
00:00:52,146 --> 00:00:53,774
I'm a veteran reporter, so…

13
00:00:53,858 --> 00:00:54,985
Turn it off.

14
00:00:58,366 --> 00:01:00,788
What does this have to do with me?

15
00:01:00,872 --> 00:01:02,458
Everything.

16
00:01:03,001 --> 00:01:04,796
It has everything to do with you.

17
00:01:06,424 --> 00:01:08,011
Oh, really?

18
00:01:08,721 --> 00:01:13,146
If I take this to the police, they will
continue investigating your brother,

19
00:01:13,229 --> 00:01:15,693
and sooner or later,
he'll be found guilty.

20
00:01:16,653 --> 00:01:21,580
After that, they will thoroughly
investigate all related parties.

21
00:01:22,707 --> 00:01:24,168
Like his family

22
00:01:24,251 --> 00:01:26,172
and you, his brother.

23
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:32,894
How much do you want?

24
00:01:34,105 --> 00:01:35,357
It's not about the money.

25
00:01:37,529 --> 00:01:39,950
You're telling me to side with Saijo?

26
00:03:00,193 --> 00:03:03,324
[farmer] It was originally
3.2 hectares wide.

27
00:03:03,408 --> 00:03:05,913
-[Saijo] Okay.
-[farmer] And there is

28
00:03:05,997 --> 00:03:08,001
a total of 375 paddy fields here.

29
00:03:08,084 --> 00:03:09,713
-Wow. All of this?
-Yes.

30
00:03:11,382 --> 00:03:13,052
And since they are on a slope…

31
00:03:13,136 --> 00:03:17,144
Those people are only concerned
about their own profits.

32
00:03:18,479 --> 00:03:23,156
They don't understand
that our agriculture is

33
00:03:23,657 --> 00:03:28,751
Japan's heart, spirit, and its future.

34
00:03:29,628 --> 00:03:33,761
I may be a member of the Watanabe Cabinet,

35
00:03:34,554 --> 00:03:36,642
but I absolutely must say this one thing.

36
00:03:38,394 --> 00:03:41,610
This country will never truly rise again

37
00:03:42,194 --> 00:03:45,492
if we don't protect the people
supporting our agricultural industry.

38
00:03:46,494 --> 00:03:48,707
[reporter on radio]
<i>When asked by reporters,</i>

39
00:03:48,791 --> 00:03:52,172
<i>Finance Minister Sosuke Saijo
made it clear he is against</i>

40
00:03:52,255 --> 00:03:56,932
<i>the Global Comprehensive Bill
currently in debate in parliament.</i>

41
00:03:57,015 --> 00:03:59,896
<i>He stated the Bill will only lead</i>

42
00:04:00,397 --> 00:04:03,236
<i>to the destruction
of Japan's primary economy.</i>

43
00:04:23,527 --> 00:04:25,280
Can't we do this over the phone?

44
00:04:28,244 --> 00:04:30,206
Tanaka from the <i>Daishin Times</i> came to me.

45
00:04:31,125 --> 00:04:34,924
He showed me a video of you with
a hostess. A video I never wanted to see.

46
00:04:36,135 --> 00:04:37,597
[panting on phone]

47
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:38,682
What?

48
00:04:39,475 --> 00:04:40,770
[gasps]

49
00:04:40,853 --> 00:04:42,648
What the hell is this?

50
00:04:44,359 --> 00:04:45,988
-She tricked me.
-[panting stops]

51
00:04:48,034 --> 00:04:52,877
But why didn't she give this video
to the police as evidence?

52
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:54,088
For money.

53
00:04:54,171 --> 00:04:57,260
If she wanted money,
she would've gone directly to you.

54
00:04:57,344 --> 00:04:58,597
Why involve someone else?

55
00:04:59,306 --> 00:05:01,895
She wouldn't get a cent
if the cops got their hands on this.

56
00:05:02,479 --> 00:05:04,609
It would be extortion
if she sent it to me.

57
00:05:05,318 --> 00:05:08,909
You mean she's indirectly threatening you
by using Tanaka?

58
00:05:08,992 --> 00:05:12,917
Tanaka's a dirty reporter.
Everyone knows he's in bed with Saijo.

59
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:16,550
That dumb hostess wouldn't even think
of doing something like this.

60
00:05:17,259 --> 00:05:20,265
What if it wasn't her? But Takeuchi?

61
00:05:20,766 --> 00:05:22,060
Takeuchi?

62
00:05:23,897 --> 00:05:28,574
[inhales sharply] Wait, didn't you say
you hold the party's swing vote?

63
00:05:29,157 --> 00:05:30,326
It's not about me.

64
00:05:31,453 --> 00:05:34,627
Someone's using me to pressure you.

65
00:05:36,673 --> 00:05:39,094
Isn't all of this your problem?

66
00:05:39,177 --> 00:05:42,977
If you hadn't done something stupid,
this would never have happened.

67
00:05:44,271 --> 00:05:46,776
[Masashi] It'll get worse
if they keep investigating.

68
00:05:47,277 --> 00:05:48,780
Then it'll be all over for you.

69
00:05:48,864 --> 00:05:50,116
Stop it.

70
00:05:50,910 --> 00:05:53,164
We're both in the same boat.
Don't forget that.

71
00:05:53,749 --> 00:05:55,209
This isn't my problem.

72
00:05:55,753 --> 00:05:58,675
Aren't they targeting you
and your swing vote?

73
00:05:58,759 --> 00:05:59,969
It doesn't matter how.

74
00:06:01,973 --> 00:06:03,017
Just fix it.

75
00:06:13,747 --> 00:06:14,958
[server] Have a seat here.

76
00:06:15,834 --> 00:06:17,045
[Shigeo] A bit more.

77
00:06:19,341 --> 00:06:21,053
-[Shigeo chuckles]
-[Nami chuckles]

78
00:06:26,856 --> 00:06:28,735
He's looking this way.

79
00:06:29,737 --> 00:06:30,781
Who?

80
00:06:30,864 --> 00:06:35,123
[chuckles] The man you saw
at the sushi place.

81
00:06:39,131 --> 00:06:41,301
Yeah, he is.

82
00:06:43,180 --> 00:06:44,851
Want to kiss?

83
00:06:46,270 --> 00:06:47,272
What?

84
00:06:54,579 --> 00:06:57,083
-[person gasps]
-[whispering, chuckling]

85
00:06:59,463 --> 00:07:00,632
[inhales deeply]

86
00:07:04,515 --> 00:07:07,228
-[chuckles]
-[Shigeo breathing heavily]

87
00:07:07,855 --> 00:07:09,024
[laughs]

88
00:07:09,107 --> 00:07:10,527
That's enough for today.

89
00:07:11,529 --> 00:07:12,573
I'll be right back.

90
00:07:13,365 --> 00:07:14,367
[clicks tongue]

91
00:07:25,181 --> 00:07:26,684
[retches]

92
00:07:28,229 --> 00:07:30,233
[breathing shakily]

93
00:07:50,732 --> 00:07:52,110
Who was that man?

94
00:07:53,279 --> 00:07:54,532
Do you like him?

95
00:07:55,449 --> 00:07:56,619
Nami!

96
00:07:58,372 --> 00:07:59,416
Are you a stalker?

97
00:07:59,499 --> 00:08:00,669
[shouting] Who is he?

98
00:08:00,752 --> 00:08:02,172
[laughs] Why?

99
00:08:03,132 --> 00:08:06,263
Did you sleep with him?
That dirty old man?

100
00:08:06,346 --> 00:08:08,184
Are you an idiot?

101
00:08:08,267 --> 00:08:10,396
It has nothing to do with you!

102
00:08:10,479 --> 00:08:13,570
Because you're a married man.

103
00:08:19,164 --> 00:08:21,168
[breathing shakily]

104
00:08:36,991 --> 00:08:38,995
[panting]

105
00:08:50,142 --> 00:08:51,144
[gasps]

106
00:09:03,085 --> 00:09:05,047
[panting continues]

107
00:09:27,342 --> 00:09:28,344
[Ichiro sighs]

108
00:09:52,058 --> 00:09:53,102
Hey.

109
00:10:01,953 --> 00:10:04,165
[informant]
You won't switch to a smartphone?

110
00:10:06,211 --> 00:10:07,213
[Ogami scoffs]

111
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:12,098
The modern phone knows more
about its owner

112
00:10:12,850 --> 00:10:15,479
than even his friends or lover do.

113
00:10:16,106 --> 00:10:19,154
-[chuckles]
-[informant] Yes. That's true.

114
00:10:19,864 --> 00:10:24,080
Carrying all your information with you
everywhere is too careless, isn't it?

115
00:10:24,874 --> 00:10:25,917
[both chuckle]

116
00:10:27,963 --> 00:10:31,804
The girl you mentioned
the other day, Ichiro's mistress.

117
00:10:32,514 --> 00:10:33,558
[Ogami] Yeah.

118
00:10:34,350 --> 00:10:38,192
[informant] She's from Fukuoka.
She came to Tokyo six years ago.

119
00:10:39,110 --> 00:10:44,329
She's always been alone,
barely dating anyone.

120
00:10:45,832 --> 00:10:52,638
That's why everyone was so surprised
when she suddenly started seeing Ichiro.

121
00:10:53,347 --> 00:10:54,349
Really?

122
00:10:55,184 --> 00:10:59,860
And her father killed himself
when she was young.

123
00:11:00,444 --> 00:11:03,075
Her mother passed away
a few years later from cancer.

124
00:11:03,910 --> 00:11:07,668
She was living with her grandmother
and brother before coming to Tokyo.

125
00:11:10,130 --> 00:11:14,055
Her father's name was Kentaro Kawabata.

126
00:11:16,644 --> 00:11:18,940
He was a government official in Fukuoka.

127
00:11:25,035 --> 00:11:28,918
Are you sure his name was Kawabata?

128
00:11:31,298 --> 00:11:34,262
Was he someone you knew?

129
00:11:35,557 --> 00:11:37,310
Only a faint memory.

130
00:11:39,690 --> 00:11:41,359
Kawabata was the name

131
00:11:42,738 --> 00:11:45,702
of the official who committed suicide
during the bubble era.

132
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:54,678
His subordinate was arrested for taking
bribes from a major securities firm.

133
00:11:55,471 --> 00:12:00,941
The police were investigating his office.

134
00:12:02,485 --> 00:12:03,988
Mr. Kawabata

135
00:12:05,324 --> 00:12:08,497
took his own life

136
00:12:10,084 --> 00:12:13,465
before the police could question him.

137
00:12:16,262 --> 00:12:18,141
Anything else you'd like to know?

138
00:12:20,730 --> 00:12:24,070
This is enough for now.

139
00:12:25,155 --> 00:12:26,199
Thank you.

140
00:12:27,619 --> 00:12:30,082
Only a "thank you"?

141
00:12:31,251 --> 00:12:32,546
I'll be grateful…

142
00:12:34,550 --> 00:12:37,806
to you until I die.

143
00:12:38,683 --> 00:12:40,687
[informant chuckling]

144
00:12:42,983 --> 00:12:44,277
Another drink?

145
00:12:45,029 --> 00:12:46,072
Sure.

146
00:12:51,584 --> 00:12:53,588
[tires squealing]

147
00:12:55,299 --> 00:12:57,804
[engine revving]

148
00:12:57,888 --> 00:12:59,432
-[tires screech]
-[gasps]

149
00:13:00,392 --> 00:13:01,771
[door opens]

150
00:13:05,444 --> 00:13:06,446
[door slams]

151
00:13:20,725 --> 00:13:22,269
[gasps]

152
00:13:22,353 --> 00:13:23,523
[driver] You happy?

153
00:13:24,106 --> 00:13:25,442
Am I done?

154
00:13:28,073 --> 00:13:30,452
I've got another job for you
if you want it.

155
00:13:31,622 --> 00:13:33,626
Please don't post that video anywhere.

156
00:13:35,337 --> 00:13:36,507
No need to worry.

157
00:13:37,133 --> 00:13:38,511
There's no more use for it.

158
00:13:39,345 --> 00:13:40,347
It won't be leaked.

159
00:13:43,103 --> 00:13:44,105
[door closes]

160
00:13:45,692 --> 00:13:47,696
[car departing]

161
00:13:55,670 --> 00:13:57,507
Did you talk with Ryu?

162
00:13:57,591 --> 00:14:00,470
Yes. He's a stubborn one.

163
00:14:01,599 --> 00:14:03,393
Do you think he's in love with her?

164
00:14:04,437 --> 00:14:05,982
That would be concerning.

165
00:14:07,026 --> 00:14:08,278
[door opens]

166
00:14:08,863 --> 00:14:10,700
Hello, Kenichi.

167
00:14:10,783 --> 00:14:11,869
Madam.

168
00:14:12,996 --> 00:14:14,248
You forgot this.

169
00:14:17,589 --> 00:14:19,008
I'll be away for a few days.

170
00:14:19,509 --> 00:14:22,807
[grunts] I see. I had no idea.

171
00:14:22,891 --> 00:14:25,772
This is more important than work.

172
00:14:29,028 --> 00:14:30,990
Call me if anything happens.

173
00:14:31,867 --> 00:14:32,911
I will.

174
00:14:34,246 --> 00:14:35,248
Have a good trip.

175
00:14:42,597 --> 00:14:44,601
[footsteps approaching]

176
00:14:55,414 --> 00:14:57,836
I'm not sure about you working.

177
00:14:57,919 --> 00:15:01,342
[sighs] Isn't it better to have
some income? No matter how small?

178
00:15:01,885 --> 00:15:04,265
[chuckles] To be working at a flower shop…

179
00:15:04,850 --> 00:15:06,562
I also have a plan, you know.

180
00:15:06,645 --> 00:15:09,776
Soon, I'll have a talk with Hide
about starting a new business.

181
00:15:10,485 --> 00:15:11,613
Oh, really?

182
00:15:12,281 --> 00:15:14,661
Then what will we do in the meantime?

183
00:15:15,621 --> 00:15:18,251
Don't you hate asking my father for money?

184
00:15:21,340 --> 00:15:25,057
I'll be at the flower shop all afternoon.
So be sure to pick up the kids.

185
00:15:31,862 --> 00:15:34,366
[Sarah, in English]
So, I read somewhere that Japan had

186
00:15:34,450 --> 00:15:36,747
the second highest adoption rate
in the world.

187
00:15:36,830 --> 00:15:38,208
Second behind the US.

188
00:15:39,085 --> 00:15:41,673
Well, I don't know
anyone who's been adopted.

189
00:15:41,757 --> 00:15:43,384
Right, 'cause here's the catch.

190
00:15:43,886 --> 00:15:47,769
Ninety-five percent of Japanese
adoptions are adult adoptions.

191
00:15:48,269 --> 00:15:51,652
So Japan has one of the lowest
adoption of children,

192
00:15:51,735 --> 00:15:54,448
but one of the highest
in adoption of adults.

193
00:15:54,533 --> 00:15:56,119
Okay. You mean <i>mukoyoshi</i>.

194
00:15:56,202 --> 00:15:58,498
-Yeah, that. <i>Mukoyoshi</i>, yeah.
-Yeah.

195
00:15:58,582 --> 00:16:05,345
Japanese do it to pass along lineage
and business successions.

196
00:16:06,807 --> 00:16:09,563
-So, <i>muku</i> -- <i>Mukoyoshi</i>.
-Yeah.

197
00:16:09,646 --> 00:16:13,988
It's only with men, right? Like,
I can't expect Japan to <i>mukoyoshi</i> a woman.

198
00:16:14,071 --> 00:16:15,073
Right.

199
00:16:15,616 --> 00:16:20,710
Actually, some of the biggest companies
in Japan have been run by adopted sons.

200
00:16:21,252 --> 00:16:23,591
Even if they have biological sons?

201
00:16:23,674 --> 00:16:25,177
-Yeah, some.
-What?

202
00:16:26,137 --> 00:16:30,855
If they find out
their biological sons are incapable.

203
00:16:32,065 --> 00:16:33,109
Wow.

204
00:16:33,652 --> 00:16:34,905
That must suck.

205
00:16:35,615 --> 00:16:38,328
Imagine your dad is like,
"Uh, son, you suck, so…

206
00:16:38,411 --> 00:16:41,209
[inhales sharply] …I'm gonna adopt
this guy who's better than you

207
00:16:41,292 --> 00:16:43,505
to run our company and be our new son."

208
00:16:45,217 --> 00:16:47,764
Japanese are sometimes
practical about things.

209
00:16:49,935 --> 00:16:52,272
Blood matters. Until it's about money.

210
00:17:03,921 --> 00:17:05,215
Here we are.

211
00:17:14,776 --> 00:17:15,987
[in Japanese] Anyone home?

212
00:17:17,489 --> 00:17:18,491
[person] Yes?

213
00:17:19,869 --> 00:17:21,455
I'll be right there.

214
00:17:25,923 --> 00:17:27,719
Who are you?

215
00:17:27,802 --> 00:17:30,641
Nice to meet you. My name is Ryu Ogami.

216
00:17:31,225 --> 00:17:34,649
I work at the NPO, JCIAA, in Tokyo.

217
00:17:35,818 --> 00:17:41,037
I am very sorry for what my husband did.

218
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:45,170
-But I have nothing more to say.
-[stutters] No.

219
00:17:46,297 --> 00:17:48,719
That's not why we're here.

220
00:17:50,180 --> 00:17:52,100
I can't help you.

221
00:17:52,685 --> 00:17:54,188
Please leave.

222
00:18:03,039 --> 00:18:06,045
[protestor] I've lived here my whole life.

223
00:18:08,299 --> 00:18:09,678
Working the land.

224
00:18:10,345 --> 00:18:13,226
Before me it was my father, grandfather.

225
00:18:14,019 --> 00:18:17,694
All my ancestors farmed this land.

226
00:18:20,115 --> 00:18:21,325
But

227
00:18:22,620 --> 00:18:26,920
there is no one to take over
after all my children left for Tokyo.

228
00:18:28,256 --> 00:18:29,509
Even so,

229
00:18:30,761 --> 00:18:33,015
I must protect this land

230
00:18:33,767 --> 00:18:36,606
that's been in my family for generations.

231
00:18:37,650 --> 00:18:43,369
All I have is this land, and now
they are trying to take it away from me.

232
00:18:44,496 --> 00:18:47,252
There should be something we can do.

233
00:18:47,837 --> 00:18:50,759
That Global Bill.

234
00:18:51,887 --> 00:18:55,226
If it passes,
it will be the end of farming.

235
00:18:55,811 --> 00:18:59,778
Greedy politicians and businesses
will swoop in to take the land.

236
00:19:00,529 --> 00:19:03,619
They'll take everything.

237
00:19:04,411 --> 00:19:09,046
He's been struggling all alone.

238
00:19:09,881 --> 00:19:11,718
Please forgive him.

239
00:19:11,802 --> 00:19:14,473
I don't care what happens to me.

240
00:19:15,266 --> 00:19:16,561
But

241
00:19:17,939 --> 00:19:21,153
don't force me off my land

242
00:19:22,155 --> 00:19:24,201
and make me die elsewhere.

243
00:19:24,284 --> 00:19:25,913
I'd like to help you.

244
00:19:27,667 --> 00:19:30,255
Who wants to buy your land?

245
00:19:30,756 --> 00:19:34,889
They aren't nice enough to just "buy" it.

246
00:19:36,392 --> 00:19:38,479
It's practically robbery.

247
00:19:39,064 --> 00:19:42,863
They offered a good price for it.

248
00:19:42,947 --> 00:19:45,243
It's not about the money!

249
00:19:46,580 --> 00:19:47,957
I will

250
00:19:49,586 --> 00:19:54,136
never sell this land. No matter the price.

251
00:19:54,846 --> 00:19:57,142
I don't think there is a need to sell it.

252
00:19:57,225 --> 00:19:59,271
You're protected by the law.

253
00:19:59,354 --> 00:20:01,275
As if the law is on my side.

254
00:20:01,985 --> 00:20:03,404
They've been

255
00:20:05,074 --> 00:20:09,751
destroying this land to make it unusable.

256
00:20:10,502 --> 00:20:12,965
To force me to leave.

257
00:20:13,550 --> 00:20:14,677
What do you mean?

258
00:20:22,860 --> 00:20:25,824
Can you see that construction site?

259
00:20:30,166 --> 00:20:33,047
It will be a chemical factory.

260
00:20:34,257 --> 00:20:37,848
If they dump their waste here,

261
00:20:37,932 --> 00:20:41,982
it will pollute the land
and make it impossible to grow anything.

262
00:20:42,983 --> 00:20:48,411
